    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Diagnostics Model Years 1999-2000 - ENGINE CONTROL SYSTEM OVERVIEW -
        ELECTRONIC CONTROL MODULE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ELECTRONIC CONTROL MODULE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Operation and Function</title>
            <figure id="f17507" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figEG1/EG1270A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Electronic Control module</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The Electronic Control Module (ECM) monitors and controls engine operation to ensure maximum
                performance and adherence to emissions standards. The ECM also monitors and regulates the vehicle cruise
                control, transmission, and starter engagement.
            </para>
            <para>The ECM controls the following:</para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Reference voltage</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Input voltage signals</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Microprocessor input and output</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Actuators</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
